.TH "AGE\-API\-QUERY" "1" "January 2020" "age-api" "age-api Manual"
.SH "NAME"
\fBage\-api\-query\fR \- Age bracket query tool
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBage\-api\-query\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads the locally stored age bracket and prints:
.IP "\(bu" 4
a machine\-readable age bracket number to standard output (stdout)
.IP "\(bu" 4
a human\-readable age bracket description to standard error (stderr)
.IP "" 0
.P
This separation allows scripting with stdout while still providing a helpful explanation for interactive use\.
.P
The age bracket is expected to be stored as an integer in the file \fB~/\.age\-api/age\-bracket\fR\.
.P
Bracket mapping:
.IP "\(bu" 4
1: Under 13
.IP "\(bu" 4
2: 13 to under 16
.IP "\(bu" 4
3: 16 to under 18
.IP "\(bu" 4
4: 18 or older
.IP "" 0
.SH "OPTIONS"
None\.
.SH "CONFIG FILE"
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB/etc/age\-api\.d/*\.conf\fR
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB/usr/local/etc/age\-api\.d/*\.conf\fR
.IP "" 0
.SH "FILES"
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fB~/\.age\-api/age\-bracket\fR
.IP "" 0
.SH "EXIT CODES"
0 Success\.
.P
1 Internal error or invalid bracket value (expected 1\-4)\.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
Machine\-readable usage (recommended for scripts):
.P
\fBage\-api\-query\fR
.P
Suppress human\-readable output:
.P
\fBage\-api\-query 2>/dev/null\fR
.P
Use the numeric bracket in a shell script:
.P
\fBage_bracket="$(age\-api\-query 2>/dev/null)"\fR
.SH "WWW"
https://www\.kicksecure\.com/wiki/age\-api
